Jeni's Splendid Ice Creams of Ohio said on Thursday that it is recalling its frozen products . 
  The company is recalling all of its ice creams, frozen yogurts, sorbets and ice cream sandwiches . 
  The listeria was found in a sample of their ice cream from a Nebraska Whole Foods store . 
  On Monday, Texas-based Blue Bell Creameries issued a voluntary recall of its products after ten people were sickened . 
  Jeni's is closing all retail stores until its products are 'ensured to be 100 per cent safe' The recall follows a similar recall by Blue Bell on Monday . 
 